data.title: Had the cinnamon roll frenchtoast
data.text: Had the cinnamon frenchtoast today. Got it togo with everything on the side. It was yummy but, very sweet. Will probably try something else next time but, will for sure go back.

data.title: Our favorite breakfast / brunch spot in Johns Creek
data.text: Be prepared to wait on weekends, but it's worth it! Part of a growing chain. Always check out the daily specials for something delicious. Lots of healthy options, too. Friendly wait staff - this place remains a regular stop for us.

data.title: Chain, but doesnt feel like one.
data.text: I have only been here for breakfast so cant comment about other seating times.  Think "upscale Denny's" with more attentive service.  Nothing exceptional, but good value for a typical breakfast.

data.title: Brunch Every Sunday
data.text:
We're at Egg Harbor every Sunday for brunch. Most of the staff know us by name and are incredibly friendly. Everyone works as a team to get all guests seated and orders in as quickly as possible. Wait times are usually under 10 minutes in the last couple hours. A couple times, we've waited 20-30 minutes, but they are happy to serve coffee or other beverages even while you wait. Seating is indoor and covered patio. There's also a second outdoor patio that's dog friendly.

The food is prepared well, and all ingredients are fresh, natural and sourced from nearby growers and suppliers. The menu is updated seasonally and each week features a couple new specials.

There are plenty of menu options for herbivores and omnivores. They are also happy to whip up your own creations.

One of my favorites from the menu are the pumpkin mini pancakes which have a whipped cinnamon butter drizzled over them. I prefer them just the way they come, but of course fresh jams and syrup are available too.

I enjoy getting a bowl of fruit with an english muffin along with sides of sliced tomatoes, avocado and a scrambled egg. Makes a great open-faced breakfast sandwich and the fruit is always super fresh.

There are a variety of coffee and juice selections, including hot brew, flavored, and cold brew coffees as well as regular and strawberry orange juices.

Definitely a popular place on Sundays, but even when it's packed out you'll have great service and feel like you've had brunch with a really big family. By far my favorite Sunday brunch spot.

data.title: Fantastic Breakfast
data.text: Loved this place, from the rooster decor - to the incredible food. Great egg dishes, super salads and burgers. Serves breakfast and lunch only. You might have to wait for a table. Wait!! this is a wonderful place...

data.title: Amazing breakfast.
data.text: Found this quaint breakfast/lunch place through online reviews on the way to the hotel. Five of us enjoyed a wonderful breakfast including pumpkin pancakes, Eggs Benedict, skillet meals, french toast and a scramble with assorted ingredients. Staff was friendly, service was great, and coffee was fresh. Try its out!!

data.title: Super duper
data.text: So impressed. So I googled best breakfast in Duluth area and landed on this place. Good location, extra great service, wide variety of breakfast items and awesome food! It was a little more expensive than I'm used to but well worth it. Our waitresses were super helpful, friendly and fast. We will definitely go back. I had scrambled white eggs with bleu cheese, Belgium waffle and chicken sausage. He had pumpkin pancakes, a super omelet and side of potatoes with fresh squeezed strawberry orange juice. We thoroughly enjoyed our meals. I love that they had chicken sausage!

data.title: Great food and service
data.text: I love the place. Great food and outstanding service. Open early so our men's bible study can meet before work.

data.title: Great Place
data.text: This is a typical Chicago breakfast place. Good food, great service, and nice ambiance. This is one of our favorite breakfast restaurants.

data.title: My favorite breakfast place
data.text: So many choices here!  This is my favorite place to go for breakfast in Johns Creek.  Food is always yummy.  Too bad there is frequently a wait.  (You can call ahead to put your name on their waiting list.)

data.title: Fabulous Brunch Option
data.text: Egg Harbor is a great brunch spot. They have a seasonal menu, which means that they use a lot of really fresh ingredients, and the flavors really come out in the food. I also really enjoyed the pancakes, which were very fluffy and filling (turns out they’re whole wheat, which I never would have guessed)! Our service was fast, but I didn’t feel rushed, which is how I like brunch. Our server was great, she had recommendations on everything when we asked, and was so great about refills and making sure we had everything we needed. Very friendly service all around. And the atmosphere of the place is great. It just seems like a really nice neighborhood spot.

data.title: Business Breakfast
data.text: Great place for business and the food was outstanding. I will be back for sure. Looking to my next visit.

data.title: Good lunch spot
data.text: Being a native from IL and Southeast WI, I'm very familiar with Egg Harbor. So glad they opened a location all the way down here. Been here several times and the food is always good. Today I had the Geneva Rosti, very good. My husband had the Chilequiles. He said it was okay, not great. Love that they give you your own "refill carafe" for the table. I suggest bringing a sweater though, the place was seriously cold. Not sure if it's like that everyday but we were absolutely freezing.

data.title: BEST EVER!!!
data.text: My husband and I drive about 30 minutes every weekend we possibly can to enjoy this place!! I have a gluten allergy and their gluten free menu is two pages long!! Delicious cinnamon rolls, pancakes, omelettes, skillet meals, and their harbor potatoes are amazing! Every time we go I can get something different and it's all delicious! The wait is never long and the service is FANTASTIC!! The kids will love the rainbow pancakes and strawberry orange juice! This place is brunch heaven for adults and kids!! Many visits and never once a bad experience or bad service.

data.title: We had seven, including three kids.  It was great!
data.text: The people were very accommodating, the food was great, and we had a really nice time.  It was a little loud in the small room we were in, but that is to be expected on a Saturday morning.  We were extremely pleased with everything!

data.title: Great food and service
data.text: I came here with my sister who is a regular here. We went on a Sunday and it was quite busy. My sister and I were told our wait was 35 minutes. I am not sure how long it took, but it wasn't bad. I don't drink coffee, but they had free coffee available outside in the waiting area, which I thought was cool. When we arrived to the table there was already water with lemon, cups, and straws on the table.The menu has a lot to choose from. I had their strawberry orange juice. It was delicious, though it comes in a small cup and there are no free refills on the strawberry orange juice, but it is defiantly something you should try. I ordered the summer in Italy french toast. You could make it a combo for $4 more, but the french toast was enough for me. The food was presented very nicely just like the picture, something which does not happen often in other restaurants. The food is a little pricey, but I think it is worth it. I paid about $15 (not including tip) for my drink and meal. Overall, the food AND service was great which makes the price worth it.

data.title: top notch service, excellent food
data.text: We enjoyed a fantastic breakfast today - everything was delicious and fresh. Pancakes were the lightest and fluffiest I've ever eaten. Our server was polite, friendly, and attentive and did those extra little things that take service from good to great. The hostess and other servers at nearby tables seemed equally friendly and polite. We got the clear impression that high quality customer service is a priority here which is always wonderful to find! We have found a new favorite breakfast spot!

data.title: Prices are out of proportion
data.text: The food is good here, but the prices are a bit too high. I ordered an omelet and the waiter asked if I wanted potatoes or fruit on the side. I ordered the fruit then was upcharged for it. Not nice.

data.title: One of our favorite breakfast places
data.text:
Service is always great. Meals vary from simple English muffin with jam all the way to the meat lovers omelette. Particularly like the combo meals which add eggs and breakfast meat to a smaller sized breakfast entree.

Coffee or decaf in pots on table makes refills easy. Side room with four tables is quieter and easier to hear conversations.

data.title: Good place for break/brunch
data.text: Just gotta love the concept of this venue ... good selection of eggs with - well with about anything.  Corn beef hash needed to be "kicked-up" a notch.  Terrific decor and vert good service ... great attitude with ALL staff.
